,Not Recommended,329430,15675512,"Posted: 3 May, 2015",all,Fatto Catto,"I really wish I could recommend this, because I really really loved the original one. I bought this game on a whim when I found out that I could import my save. To save time for others:TL;DR: Save your money if you already have the original game, because the new content does not validate the price. If however you havent got the game at all, it is worth paying for as the old one is no longer available on steam.Positive aspects:-returning players from SoD get access to an exclusive player with the Nimble trait (reflexes)-new type of car added that has an increased trunk space (6 spaces) with a bit less handling than a modern pickup, but more readily available and just as sturdy.-like original SoD has intergrated controller support available-returning players can import their save from SoD, breakdown and Lifeline-Actions like creating more snacks and coffee are now available at the kitchen-new mission type included in story type and breakdown, gives new lease of life to objects such as timers and talking dolls-new map icons make it easier to see at a glance what kind of missions are available to youNegative aspects:-The game is really badly optimized. This particular game lags even on minimum specs-Some zombies are not rendered correctly, and sometimes the buildings have the same problem. For machines (like mine) that ran original SoD perfectly fine, it seems like this is an issue that shouldn't have been one.-the map looks less smooth and more boxy and cartoonish-for the content that has been added ontop of the old version, it really is not worth the money even with the discount. The added features included in this pack, i would only realistcally pay around £8 at most.-No new voice actors have been commissioned. For when playing breakdown and the like, it can get tiresome to hear the same 6 voice actors over and over in different pitches.-at times, attacks do not connect to the zombies, leading you to waste your stamina swinging wildly while they still come and wreck you.-it is commonplace for your character to glitch into the foundations of the building. Whereas in the original SoD this glitch was only really common for zombies, the glitch has now expanded to affecting player characters-the graphics as a whole just look sharp and horrible as if no edge smoothing has been used at all. in all honesty, I prefer the graphics of the old game.Conclusion:I will probably continue to play this game as i have already spent money on it, but looking back I wish I saw a review like this instead of the generic ""This is a ♥♥♥♥♥♥ cash grab"" so i could have just happily stayed with the original.However, if you've never played State of Decay at all, it is a brilliant game, and will recommend you buy this copy as the old one is now not available."
