76561197983767679,Recommended,329430,23145567,"Posted: 22 May, 2016",all,Knox,"I have to recommend this game. I cannot in good conscience not do so. You see, I came late to the party, and so bypassed the controversy that followed the release of this 'Year One Edition', which includes the dlcs Breakdown and Lifeline.If you have not played State of Decay, then pay no attention to SOME of the reviews for this game, they are very much biased and tainted by that controversy that happened long ago which you can read more about in one of the other reviews I am sure.This game has a lot going for it. It is very close to the type of zombie-game I was looking for for many years. An actionpacked 3rd person game, much in the style of some earlier 'GTAs', with a focus on base- and resource management.Gather your group of survivors,  recruit new people, complete missions and interact with other survivor-groups. Scavenge for resources to use in upgrading and protecting your base and people; or move your entire base elsewhere on the map! All in a semi-open world yours to explore. Just be careful! Cars may break down, and if you get caught alone during the night by a horde be prepared to run!A word about the dlc Lifeline. To some extent, I found this campaign to almost more enjoyable than the base game. Maybe it was just the setting, which is more urban in Lifeline. The mechanics are the same, although you cannot move your base around in Lifeline. This doesnt matter, as the base you start with in this dlc has a lot of potential and is scene to some great defensive action. Call in snipers and air support as you try to defend your base of operations when the hordes get alerted to your presence, before gathering up your most experienced soldiers and go on a supply run, or try to rescue VIPs.Also. State of Decay has permadeath for your survivors, and actions may have consequences. I lost one of my earliest party members because I didn't get his medicine in time... I didn't know there was an actual time-limit. Be prepared to deal with it!I experienced no bugs, crashes or any other technical issues worth mentioning with the game as of early 2016. No worries.There arent many of these types of games in the 'zombie-genre', which I think is a shame. If you think the same, then I highly recommend Year One Edition to any newcomers.All the best."
