and or no weapons dealer the very rare guns are basically impossible to get. It really needs balancing and the supplies need to be better distributed.Breakdown. The main DLC to play is a nice idea in theory but rapidly becomes boring. All that changed are the zombies slowly level up as you go. I cant believe theres 100 levels of breakdown, My personal best is 6, then i get bored and play something else. With no variation in levels you always start a level, loot the army bases looking for the rare guns, then build up which ever base is your favourite. Theres no side missions or random events to keep the levels fresh, its just a rinse and repeat affair. The only thing that keeps you going is the hope you stumfble along a new weapon, but its not really enough to base a game around.All in all its a game that shows lots of promise but gets let down by a few massive issues that just sap the fun from the game."
