76561198243702432,Not Recommended,329430,27594173,"Posted: 25 November, 2016",all,Qingu,"I had fun with this game, but I can't recommend it due to a number of issues.The story:The storyline is extremely bland and forgettable. The story takes place in a cookie-cutter American zombie apocalypse universe. No suprises here. The characters and dialogue are just as bland as the setting. In all fairness, the storyline in Lifeline is actually somewhat interesting. It's still not great, but it actually has some suspense and drama to carry it forward.The voice acting:It seems like the minor survivors are voiced by 2, maybe 3 actors in total. I was regularly saving survivors with the same voice as Marcus. You'll hear the same lines of dialogue over and over again. Many of the character models are recycled too, it seems.The gameplay:The combat is pretty fun. Popping zombie skulls open with a well-placed bullet is always fun - can't really go wrong with that. The melee combat isn't too bad either. It's all pretty simple, but I don't really have any big complaints.Mechanics:Base management is simple and boring. There's no real strategy or depth to it. It feels really lazy, and it's a big missed opportunity to add some much-needed depth to the game. Base defense is buggy and obnoxious.My biggest complaint about the game is inventory management. There are several different types of painkillers that do the exact same thing but take up separate precious inventory slots. Weapons occupy backpack slots, whether or not you're holding them in your hands. The trunks and truckbeds in this game are the size of a suitcase apparently. A small pistol takes up the same amount of space as a grenade launcher. There's a weight system, but it only really exists to punish you for carrying the wrong combinations of items - it's not something you really care about, it's just an annoyance. You'll find yourself making constant trips back to base to drop off loot. I feel like I spent most of the game tediously managing my inventory and running loot back to my base.Summary:Driving around running over zombies is pretty fun. And there are lots of different guns to shoot zombies with, which is fun. But unfortunately the game suffers from a depressing lack of depth and polish."
