76561197970537402,Recommended,329430,25475525,"Posted: 12 September, 2016",all,Gabriot,"This is the closest thing to a proper single player zombie game that's ever been invented.  I recommend this game hesitently knowing how scummy the devs are that made the game (they released a very buggy game and then re-released it with bug fixes and charged full price rebranding it as a new game).  That being said, the game is actually so good I'm willing to put aside my morals and say if you are looking for a proper single player zombie game, this is the best that you will find.It still has some bugs, and there are many things I wish they would change, but overall the game kicks♥♥♥♥♥Things I wish were changed:-I wish they made the game mod-able so we could see awesome community driven content-I wish there was a proper element of human vs. human combat and politics.  As it stands the game is really just humans vs. zombies-I wish there were more maps for the sandbox mode, or better yet randomly generated maps-Along the same lines I wish you could make your base in any structure on the map-I wish that the ""management"" aspects of the games allowed you to pause the game.  I'd like to review my characters while back at home base and make plans for my base without half a day worth of gametime passingThings I love about this game:-The combat is very well done.  When you are overwhelmed by zombies there is always a chance to beat the odds and survive, which feels absolutely epic when you pull it off, but at the same time the brutal death scenes and permadeath make the death sting that much more. This entire portion of the game is beautifully executed.  A+-The base building and managment aspects of the game are far better than I expected.  It is so fun having a base and a community of survivors you have to care for.  This is one of the coolest aspects of the game and something I haven't seen properly done in any other zombie games (they usually just focus on you as a sole survivor).  There's room for improvement here but as it stands it is the best you'll get from this genre of games.-If you are a fan of The Walking Dead, this is the closest game you will find to emulating that experience.-The map is very well designed and the main storyline was actually pretty decent.Overall it's the best Zombie game out there and I don't foresee any others surpassing it any time soon unless some amazing Fallout 4 zombie mod gets made.  If you can look past your morals and just buy this version of the game you'll have a good time."
,Recommended,329430,33288047,Posted: 5 July,all,Consuela,"I had an eye on this game for quite a while.  I thought the concept of creating your own community and switching characters within that community was interesting.  But after reading reviews, I saw many people found this game to be dissapointing, pointing out glitches, bugs etc. and mostly complaining about the price mainly because they were forced to rebuy the game for minor upgrades.  I was very skeptical, but after waiting until yesterday, one day before the end of the steam summer sale, I decided to roll the dice and give the game a chance.And by all means THIS GAME IS NOT BAD AT ALLSure, it has glitches, but they're very minor and not gamebreaking.  All games are like that.  No crashes so far, no graphical glitching.  Overall this game is very stable.  The only glitches that are encountered are the animations, which most games have problems with, so no biggy there.  (I did see another review posted before mine saying that it's so buggy that it takes away from the game....it does not at all.)This game provides alot of content, not even including the DLC.  The only problem that I find somewhat dissapointing with this game is that you can't have enemies or rival communities, so no survivor vs. survivor ordeals.  Although this threw me for a loop, it's still quite enjoyable since you're not worrying too much about being shot at.  The Zombie A.I. is pretty nice.  They react to sound as they should, and they're not too tough and not too easy.  You mainly need to worry about the special zombies (I've been ripped in half by a feral twice on breakdown.)Now for the price of the game...is a big downside.  I paid $9.81 USD for this game, and I'd say it's well worth it for that much.  $30.00 USD for this game seems alittle much if you're like me and have to limit what you can buy.  However, if you're able to catch this game during a sale or can just throw out $30 like nothing, then by all means, buy this game.  If worse comes to worse, give it an hour and a half and see how you like it.  If you hate it, refund it.Overall, this game may seem a bit pricey, but for a good sale I'd say this game is well worth a try."
