,Recommended,329430,29769820,Posted: 7 February,all,Shooter Swag,"Overall:  Yes, recommended.  It has a story line that is above-average, game-play is above-average, graphics are above-average (considering when made).  Everything is essentially above-average.  It needs a bit of work, but still worth buying, especially on sale.Pros:Story - A bit fast-paced at times, without much explanation for the ""why"", but it's not the worst.  Immerses the player adequately.Playable Characters - Each character seems unique and has their own personality.  I believe there are over 100+ characters/NPC's in game.  Characters/NPC's will bicker between each other and do small missions (i.e. scavenging) on their own.  A nice touch.  Makes the base camp feel like the NPC's are contributing without you having to do everything.  They also defend the base on their own.Game-play - needs some polish, but it's still enjoyable.  Melee (blunt, edged, heavy weapons, etc.), gun-fighting (all types of pistols, rifles, SMGs, shotguns and sniper rifles), and vehicles (cars, trucks, SUVs) sum up the way to kill zombies.3rd person perspective only - pro or con based on your taste.  Works great while outside.Base-building - definitely one of the best characteristics.  Build up the infirmary, food storage, tower, workshop, etc. to provide various benefits for your group.RGP-like - can level up various skills.  Not very intricate/complex, but enjoyable.Weapons degrade over time and need to be repaired.Scavenging - fun to scavenge.  Grab a survivor to watch your back though, especially at night, and hop in a car (more cargo space than your backpack).Radio - can call in scavengers to help bring back supplies, back-up (SWAT), artillery, new home base relocation, etc.  Of course, you have to complete missions to unlock many of these.2 other DLC's that are included in YOSE which change things up a bit.Cons:3rd person only - pro or con.  Can be problematic when entering buildings and small rooms.  Cannot see threats until the character is fully in the room due to 3rd person.-Driving - one area that really needs a patch.  It...just...doesn't....feel right...the turning and handling is a bit strange; also, accelerating and decelerating does a weird zoom in & out which distorts vision - hard to drive and recon the area b/c of it.-Closing Doors - ugh, an area that is very annoying.  Sometimes you'll close them without a problem, other times you have to maneuver the character a bit before you can close doors (time consuming) - not good when being chased by a zombie horde.-NPC's / AI - weird glitches occasionally such as:  will stop accompanying you for no reason - happened twice to me; when escorting AI to destination, they've stopped moving just outside the objective (I had to physically push them into the objective to complete the mission - happened twice).  Companions like to block doorways - not game breaking, just an annoyance, you can roll through them or even push them out of the way.  They also like to spazz out and take their time when loading into vehicles - again, not game breaking, just needs a patch.Rated 7 out of 10."
