76561198012626337,Recommended,329430,30073529,Posted: 20 February,all,Hellios Rayearth,"Survival Zombie-RPG ALMOST done right. This game is what I had hoped Dead Island and Dying Light would be on release.Gameplay:9/10Survival Aspect of the game went above and beyond my expectations and probably the best one I’ve experienced in this genre:-	Declining Group Resources-	Timed Missions-	Community Building/Morale-	Camp upgrades-	Character perma-deathYou have all of these aspects to manage, all while trying to keep your played characters alive during missions, which incidentally update simultaneously, adding more pressure to your already stressful playing environment.RPG Aspect of the game is what I feel took a hit. Character building is fairly shallow. Aside from the general character stats, there isn’t enough character development in-game. Skills are fairly shallow and doesn’t do much to differentiate playable characters from each other, aside from their weapon specialization.Graphics:7/10Not the prettiest of games, but that was never a strong point of this genre. Dying Light was probably one of the few exceptions to this, and maybe RE 5/6/7 (although I can hardly classify RE5&6 as Survival Zombie RPG). Regardless, it passes as an ok-game in terms of visuals.Music and Sound:8/10Music in-game gives me a very Left 4 Dead-esque impression. Aside from Nostalgia, tension in the game is really well matched by its music and ambience. I think it’s really well done.As for voice-acting, it’s fairly bland, you can also easily notice recycled voices. This, however, I can forgive. Western RPG Games, in general, has yet to catch up to Japan’s voice-acting quality in terms of game characters only Bethesda, Bioware, Ubisoft and some select W&B games really stand out.Plot and Story:6/10I haven’t gone too far in the game yet to make a credible conclusion, however, I’m not impressed so far. However, this in my opinion is also forgivable, being that the game is a Zombie-Surival RPG game. The premises of the game itself limits the variety in story I think.I highly recommend this game to fans of the genre, but if you are a perfectionist I’ll give my warning ahead of time. There are just too many instances that can happen that will “F*** up” your perfect run. If you’re this type of gamer, be ready to restart your gameplays at least a couple of times."
