76561198026362340,Recommended,329430,33018234,Posted: 29 June,all,Pill Cosby,"aside from the shadow bug (fix below) it is a great game!""aydark  has State of Decay: Year-One Jul 5, 2015 @ 8:10pmI have flickering shadows as well, on GTX 770 here. For me, it's related to using 16:10 aspect ratio (my monitor is 1920x1200 resolution). It's just one of the bugs related to that aspect ratio. Undead Labs is aware of the issue, but I haven't heard anything about a patch yet.If this is the same problem for you (that you run 16:10 aspect ratio), then try this workaround (which works 100% of the time for me).1) Move the camera around until you are looking at one of the glitched shadows (I usually use a large tree or the power lines in town, which shadows show up as zig zags on the road).2) Open the display options, change the aspect ratio to 16:93) Go back to the gameplay and wait a few seconds, the shadows will ""reset"" and work properly4) Go back to the display options, change the aspect ratio back to 16:105) Go back to the gameplay and the shadows should reset again and be working properly.Sometimes, I have to try options 2 - 5 two or three times, but it eventually works. Unfortunately, I have to do this every time I start the game up.. but the shadows remain working for the rest of that session at least."""
