,Recommended,329430,32087446,Posted: 31 May,all,h.barkas,"The main problem with the game are the bugs. It starts with setting the resolution. Interestingly the game doesn't accept 1440p, it's either 1080p or 4K. Another thing is the quality setting which is restricted to max by default although you can get a modded config from the nexus that unlocks ultra settings. There you can also get 2K texture packs and other mods to enhance your gameplay experience.The most annoying bug are the flickering shadows in 4K that can drive you crazy. There's a no-shadow mod to circumvent the problem but I think that's not a valid option to fix this bug. Better try Realistic Shadows Mod - SweetFX - FOR VANILLA - FOR BREAKDOWN - FOR LIFELINE by SilentResident on the nexus.The zombies clipping through walls are a minor issue in comparison.All these bugs that still exist after years hold the game back from being a great game instead of being only above average.Despite the bugs which can mostly be squashed using mods it's an interesting game and you can experience memorable moments while playing. The game world is detailed and large with no loading screens thanks to the CryEngine.I can't recommend the game at full price. Although it's well worth your money if it goes on sale for under €10 and if you have the patience to do some work on polishing the game yourself with mods. In the condition SOD is sold I rate it 6.5, with mods it is 8.5/10."
