76561198045147690,Recommended,329430,28246009,"Posted: 7 December, 2016",all,[ONS]Emanouche,"Got this on Xbox 360 when it first came out, so technically I probably have over 50-60 hours playing it combined. It was the only reason I kept coming back to playing my xbox at the end of the life cycle. Amazing, you build a community of survivors and you have to scavange the map for resources and such. Original SOD is awesome and story driven. All DLCs are included in this version of the game: Breakdown DLC, is pretty much sandbox game in which you can play at building your community up until you run out of ressources to scavange in the map, then you can move on and start over carrying a few survivors over with you and doing so increases the difficulty. Also you survivors (in all game modes) can perma-death, which adds to the tension. Lifeline DLC is another story mode in a new map that let's you play as the military; that means, more guns GUNS GUNS, haha. Overall the complete package is a must buy, get it on sale if you've already played it in it's original form, don't hesitate if it's your first time (unless you want to, I'm not your dad). It's a game I will always go back to... until State of Decay 2 comes out at least.EDIT: This game when it first came out was 2nd only to Minecraft on XBLA sales."
