76561198095662537,Recommended,329430,29594038,Posted: 30 January,all,Bøll3mis 🤙🏻,"State of Decay is one of the best zombie games out there. If you like slaying hordes of zombies, building bases, awesome meele attack animations, nice cars, characters with personality, horror and lots of fun this is the game just for you!Firstly I would like to point out, that the game is very beautiful, the animations are amazing and lifelike.Your journey takes place in Trumbull Valley, which is a rather large open world filled with lots of zombies. Your mission is to escape the Valley, while you try to survive and gather as many followers as possible. A great difference with this game and other games in the same genre is, that when a follower/character dies it stay death. At first I was really shocked as I lost a character in the beginning of the game, and was sitting back with mixed feelings, because I already felt that I bonded with the character. So you have to be careful, when you are exploring. Loosing a character might affect the way that your game plays out in the end.The two DLCs are fun as well. The Breakdown DLC is almost the same as the originally game, tho there is no main mission line. Your mission here is to fix a truck to move on to the next level (same map but increased difficulty), you begin at level 1 and it goes all the way to level 99. So if you love grinding and killing millions of zombies this DLC will fall right in your taste!The Lifeline DLC is in another map, where you this time follow the millitary aspect of the zombie apocalypse. Your mission is to survive wave after wave of zombies that attack your base while you are extracting civillians and VIPs. This DLC has different endings, which depends on the choices that you make during the game.Overall I would like to say, the sounds are very realistic, nice voice actors, the visual is damn neat. Only con I would like to add is, that the main mission line is very short and it could have been a lot longer. Maybe we will see that in State of Decay 2? I am very excited!So should you buy this game? 28 euro is a cheap price for a game of this size! If you like the aspects of roaming from GTA, crafting from Minecraft and zombies from The Walking Dead, this is just the game for you!Be aware, when you rush out excited to smash some zombie skulls be careful, this is not like Left 4 Death, you can't just take 20 zombies on you and beat them by meele. Max is 3, more than that you'll get overrrun if you are alone fighting with meele!Now lets purge this world of zombies!"
