76561198062263329,Recommended,329430,32004773,Posted: 27 May,all,Dr GoodBudz,"It's hard not to like this game. With these few exceptons.Missions hit you at the speed of light and your the only one who can do them. Why have a camp full of survivors? They just hang out and wait for you to take controle of them. If you send them out to scavange 75% of the time they'll end up needing your help anyway, so why bother?Zombies will spawn feet from you during any fight so gauging weather or not you can handle a situation on your own is almost impossible. they almost always spawn out of camera view and get a surprise grab on you. Even if your dead quiet most times zombies will hone right in on you in grupes that weren't visibly there seconds ago.Cars fall apart way to fast even though they are the best way to take out hords in a timely fashion and zombies will glue themselves to your vehicle every time, causing you to to do even more damage trying to get them off. I have seen them fly twenty of thirty feet to do this. All the while grabbing onto parts with no visible place to hold onto.AI partners will give up during large fights and submissively crouch, causing you to waist more stamina to help them, putting you at risk. So it's better to just go alone. They also don't use guns in their inventory.Walls to your base are just there for show, zombies will hop over them with ease even if reinforced with barbed wire. This happens with doors in the game too. Zombies will just glitch right through them while your barricading a house.The barricade missions are flat out stupid. The point is to barricade yourself safely inside but the only way to beat the mission is to kill all the zombies trying to get inside? So you barricade all the windows then stand outside and kill the zombies running at the building. Why?Making a loud noise while serching for resources isn't situatinal. Meaning if you make a loud noise while searching an area you've already cleared the game will just spawn in a mess of zombies for you to deal with. So trying to go fast is like playing russian roulette.Missions will spawn on all sides of the map in a game where every mission is on a time limit, giving you absolutely no time to walk around and explore. It's a constant sprint to the next mission. Granted you don't have to complete all the missions to do well. But that dosent stop the chick on the radio from constantly telling you your running out of time to do them.You will learn to hate the question, ""What did you get?"" And the answer  ""Aww you know... Stuff""Also the least enduring statment ""I hope you brought me somthing pretty.""This game does have it's moments and it's hard not to see the potential the sequel will have that should be coming out soon. But if they don't take into consideration some of the shotcomeings this game has on the whole. We're all in for a painful ride. I'll be waiting to see how the feedback stacks up befor taking a chance on it. Note that I got this game on sale for about eight bucks and if Steam had a neutral button I'd probibly give it that. But untill then I'd say wait to see how the next one plays out. Or give this one a shot with these problems in mind."
