,Recommended,329430,25107852,"Posted: 24 August, 2016",all,Insy,"Intro TL;DRThis is a 3:rd person scavenge and survival action game with RPG elements. It is set in a post-apocalyptic setting where most people died and then stood up again.This game is for you if you like exploring under tension,running slightly simple mission and building a small society.These are the things you need to be able to overlook.-    Auto save that you have absolutely no control over.-    Game world has poor and inconsistent persistence. Zombies often spawn in when you can see them.Cars can get repaired whilst doing nothing. Areas don't stay cleared (due to random spawn-ins)-    Some of the missions you get are of a ""You're a school teacher who needs to hold everyone’s hand""-type-    Game can be repetitive. Some missions feature you haveing a talk with a given character. When you for the fifth time do that mission with the exact same dialogue it just feels lazy.-    The game has no Cooperative play mode. This could seriously mitigate most of the negatives.-    The menus are cumbersome to use.-    I've built at least a few facilities because I clicked one to many times on something whilst finding out what that facility was.-    You cannot cancel facility being built-    Physics are twitchy. Be careful about flipping your car full of loot...A few tips for enjoying the game.Whenever a slightly different mission shows up. Do it. You'll get enough of the repetitive ones anywayUse the radio tower to find resources you need.Recruit people when you canExtend the base as much as possible.Don't be afraid to move.Build outposts around the base. Really does help.What did I like about it?+    Big gameworld to explore. Nothing is locked down. Go out there and explore.+    A bunch of characters to choose between.+    Characters actually die and are gone from play after that.+    You do have some control over how the settlement survives based on resources gathered, facilities built and outposts settled+    Game has a mechanism for how much sound you make. It works pretty well.+    I like the palette"
