76561198034013908,Recommended,329430,29774853,Posted: 7 February,all,brthrgrim,"I do recommend this game.  Some people apparently find the combat system to be ""clunky"" but seems just fine to me.  Enjoyed base building, little missions, world, etc.Lots of caveats though!This game has a ridiculous amount of bugs.  Nothing seemed to be fixed from the non YOSE versions.  Not too bad if you always keep an eye out for them.  Zombies WILL randomly go through walls and doors.  Sometimes it will just be ""cosmetic"", as in you can see them but they can't see you or hit you.  Sometimes they will just flat out run through things.  You may also accidentally run through walls or closed doors when you least expect it.  Most annoying thing is when the gates in Lifeline no longer exist for the zombies.  It seems you can reset the issue by running down and opening and closing the gates.  But kind of disappointing when a whole horde of zombies just phases through your closed gate.If you alt tab to look at anything else on your computer, you will be stuck in a non full sized game window.  You have to exit the game fully and re enter to fix this.Be careful driving.  Sometimes hitting even small objects with your vehicle at relatively low speeds can make it fly through the air and crash.  If a vehicle is upside down, it will automatically explode after a minute or so, no exceptions.  So if you have sacks in it, you'll want to rapidly unload them or lose everything.Your NPC allies tend to be incredibly stupid.  They don't seem to use silencers, so if they go with you to fight, be aware that they will use melee weapons only, even if their life is in danger.  They also will sometimes suicide, so if they say ""clear out, I've got these guys!"", listen to them and clear out.  They may use an incendiary or explosive.  I've had my vehicle blown up by an NPC doing this next to me, which basically killed me too.  They may also freeze, not fighting the zombies or doing anything else.  I've had refugees do this as well as a fellow soldier on base.  For the refugees, I was able to push them outside, then push them all the way to base with a car, then inside.  They remained frozen until picked up by helovac.All this being said, this is one of the few games I've played through many times and am still playing!  Hoping all these issues disappear with SoD 2, when they use the Unreal engine instead of the Cry something or other engine.  Assuming it was named ""Cry"" because when you play a game with it, most of the time you just want to cry due to the poor quality."
