,Recommended,329430,18966742,"Posted: 8 November, 2015",all,Sin,"This game is exactlty the same as the non-YOSE edition, except with all the DLC included and a couple minor things, more car skins... etc.   The graphics dont look much better if at all better than the original on PC.  If you were to buy one of them definintely buy this one, but dont buy both unless you're a huge fan.  Highly recommend this game, it's been a while since i played it now and everytime i see screenshots for it i get the itch to play it and it's hard to resist it...  may be one of my favourite games of all time, and i've been playing a long time...My original review for the non YOSE edition:Longest review i've written, and i dont like long reviews but i cant stop talking about it.I recommend anyone who tried this game to play at least until you've gotten to the church, which is fairly early on. I stopped playing it as i didn't understand the point of the game or what to do. Not a lot is explained to you very well but you can figure it out over time. I get really engaged in this game and it feels very real. When your favourite character dies, they're gone forever. No loading a savegame to bring them back.In the game, you can drive vehicles plowing through hordes, gather resources, rescue survivors, change home base locations to better suit your needs and build and upgrade your base as well for other purposes. There is a storyline and a definitive ""end"" to the main game, which i was worried it didn't have at first. However, the ""Breakdown"" DLC allows you to keep playing the game forever by reaching the next level after repairing an RV each time and driving to a new location, which is just the same exact map that has been completely reset except on higher difficulty (up to level 6 i believe, afterwards it's the same difficulty).I highly recommend this game, i cannot stop playing it, and i definately recommend the ""Lifeline"" DLC as it's a new map and more of a story based timeline, with daily seiges on your base you have to defend. More ammo and supplies are available in this DLC also. You also get to drive on abandonded highways and get caught in ""Danger Zones"" which is fun too.Only problem i have with this game is you never see anyone else on the map outside their camps, no one else is ever driving around, walking around (unless walking home from a mission, even if you're there to drive them home). You friends in the game never use guns or the weapons in their hands either when fighting. A lot of people criticize the way your friends go on missions and get stuck and never seem to do anything on their own. I actually like this, it gives you more to do. The game does get a little repetitive after a while too but if you switch between the DLCs it changes it up. Another problem which is debatable, is that time passes by without you actually being game, even though it's an offline game. The game simulates the time spent offline (to a point) when you start the game next. Despite all this i'm not sure this game could be any better."
