76561197996384693,Recommended,329430,21445309,"Posted: 25 February, 2016",all,1st_Warlord,"Do not understand how this review got marked a few times for not being helpful? Oh well..State of Decay: YOSE Day One Edition despite the negativity for this game due to previous owners concerns, it is a great game to play. Purchased the game while on sale and was not disappointed at all with the overall gameplay. While playing the run-through of State of Decay Year-One, it was rather challenging but yet balanced to keep up the stamina of the characters.  The Breakdown edition is very balanced as you get to higher levels. The Lifeline edition is a great story line to follow to the end twice since you need to in order to get both achievements.With the Breakdown and Lifeline DLC with State of Decay Year-One edition is great package.My personal complaints are:Lily broadcasts seems to pester a little too much at times about other tasks when you wish to secure your home site stockpiles. The way I managed to search all the buildings and it helped to level up the characters Maya and Marcus with less difficulties, is to perform those searches before entering the church at the start. After sufficiently searched and found the needed stocks, only then enter the church to continue on with the storyline.The characters and zombies can walk on water and do not swim.My personal suggestions are:The pick-up trucks and SUVs should have more available room then 6 slots since they do have more space in reality to toss the duffle bags inside. Something like 10 would be reasonable.It would have been awesome to have multiplayer sessions of the game. To have a real community together to secure resources and defenses for the home site.Would like to have seen a home site big enough to implement all the facilities that you can add for the site. It could have had a home site requirement of 20 survivors needed and 75 building materials.Having 8 outposts is sufficient but it would have been even better if they were setup as mini-sites that you could lock in survivors into position on the roof to snipe oncoming zombies and you must maintain their stock levels in order to keep up the defenses and not just placing the standard mines for the surrounding area.Even though the game map is big; it just still seems rather small after playing for a while. Having a bigger map area would have been awesome.As mentioned in complaints above but now noted as a suggestion here, the swimming ability. If you were to swim in the polluted waters (filled with dead zombies) you could get sick compared to swimming in clear waters.I could continue to add to the list but it is still a great game to play. I do hope that the developers “Undead Labs” will continue with this game and create a great series/add-ons with it with all the suggestions made from so many players listed here and their forums.Also, thank you to so many players on Steam that created great guides to obtain the achievements, it helped a whole lot."
