,Recommended,329430,15781418,"Posted: 10 May, 2015",all,Jaro,"With all the negative reviews, I feel I have to do this release some justice.I have spent 110 hours on the original and 35 hours on this remastered version already.For newcomers, State of Decay is an innovative zombie survival with an open-world ""GTA""-esque vibe to it.There is no other game on the market that fills the gap like this and considering the huge modding community for State of Decay, I strongly believe that this is a ""love it or hate it"" game. I cannot stop playing Breakdown.The definitive version looks stunning remastered in 1080p with new objectives and game mechanics. You can also import your original save files.As for bugs, there are a few minor which are common to the open-world genre, but there has not been one instance where my gameplay or immersion have been interrupted and there are certainly no new bugs with this release.Having said all that, for those who did not enjoy the original State of Decay, this release will not change your mind.I advise prospective buyers to read up on the new features and watch some gameplay before deciding whether to purchase.Do not be too easily put off by the negative reviewers who were disappointed after asking Santa Claus for too many presents.Sincerely, Aslan"
