76561198014313584,Recommended,329430,22736283,"Posted: 30 April, 2016",all,chadtindale,"I don't know how to recommend this game enough. If I could impress upon you the ""why"" you play games, it'd definitely make you feel like a zombie apocolypse was something you could live through... Or not... There's just so much to this game...But here are some things you might be expecting which will dampen an otherwise fun experience...1) The graphics aren't the most amazing. They're perfect for this game, but this isn't made in the Unreal engine and it's not that type of game. It's got a lot of things to put on the screen and very few walls between them, so expect medium view distances, and lots of ""adequate"" graphics.2) No seriously, the graphics. This was originally an indy download game on the XBLA, so it wasn't shooting for the stars. There's a lot of short cuts, like how blocky putting up baricades can be. The graphics repeat a lot, Not every limb will fly off a zombie in a unique manner, it's just not aiming for that kind of game...3) The action isn't fast paced. It can be at times, but for the most part, you're questing in a zombie apoc world. Running errands, or looting to keep your home base in order. That's the bread and butter of the game. If you're looking for scary wall to wall thrills, you'll find this game wasn't designed for you.4) The game isn't going to tell you how to play. There's a fun leveling up system... it won't tell you how to use it. There's a neat system for maintaining your home base... it won't tell you how to use it. If you're not willing to experiment on the game a bit to figure it out, this can be frustrating.5) There are glitches. About 4-5 times through a straight play through... you're going to get something that defies physics. Whether a zombie runs through a closed door, A car gets trapped in a porch, or a feral zombie goes flying across the gap between you... I know it sucks, but for the most part, the game is very fun, and those errors won't dampen the experience much if you're ready for them.6) You're determined to not like new things... If you want a game that could be described as ""Like Call of Duty with..."" or ""Like Resident Evil... "", then this is the wrong game. I've honestly never seen such a good blend of action and strategy. You're gonna have to come up with a plan for how your team gets by. And your second play through will be more enjoyable than your first. Honestly, I'm on my fourth, and it's the most fun yet. You have to learn what you can slack on, and what you can't put off. It's a unique experience, and that's probably its best quality.If you keep all that in mind, and don't forget that there's mods you can pick up on Nexus and stuff, this game is great. It's one of the only games I've bought that I keep returning to play. I play it again and again. I love the DLC... I love the alternate modes. And I love the voice acting. This game can be greatly engaging... Or it can be a disappointment, depending on if you're open to what the game is, and not what you hoped it would've been instead."
