,Recommended,329430,15719529,"Posted: 6 May, 2015",all,OldWorld,"Whilst a very obvious console port, if you can forgive the game for it's poorer aspects (melee combat doesn't feel completely fluid, zombies don't render well at distances, blurred textures, low dynamic shadow distance), you will have a blast. Big map, driveable vehicles, lots of items, customization, base/community building. Definitely worth the price in my opinion. Far from an 'AAA' title, but it has it's own charm.Pros:*Graphics are better than original release (albeit not significantly)**Seems better optimized than the original release (from what I've tested I'm getting pretty-much a solid 60fps on Ultra)***Very easy to mod (hordes of zombies, zombies do more damage, remove lit-up containers, remove zombie radar icons)****Mods for the original game work on YOSE too*****Map is a decent size******Breakdown especially is very fun, lots of different characters, difficulty increases*******An abundance of different items, weapons, levelling********Different zombie types, adds to the excitement/fear without being too far-fetchedCons:*No anti-aliasing**Assisted-aim with a controller can't be turned off***Lootable containers (wardrobes etc) glow white, which kills immersion. Google: No More X-Ray Eyes to disable****A hunger system would've been cool, but stamina forces you to eat which is an okay compromise*****Can be buggy, can't climb on certain objects, etc******I sometimes encounter a bug where if I die, and start a new character, a sound repeatedly replays which is incredibly irritating. Restart game to fix.7/10. Not the best game I've ever played, but worth it for a cheap price. I'd happily pay £20-$30 for it. Can definitely get a decent number of hours out of it. Just don't expect perfection."
