76561198020462798,Recommended,329430,27089778,"Posted: 24 November, 2016",all,azzizzle,"This game has been much maligned because it's essentially a realllllyy expensive DLC and remake of the original State of Decay. If you look at the negative reviews here, the real issue you'll find is that this game was not simply given to people who already supported the company by playing it. Please understand though, that that's really the only big issue with this game. If you are a first time player, you will LOVE this game!The gameplay in this game is really just good and simple fun: think GTA style movement and map all centered around the zombie apocalypse. It sounds odd, but believe me, it really works. It also combines some management of resources, but mainly centers around 3rd person action. There are also 3 modes providing really good replay value: there's the chill and fun story mode, there's the ramp-up in difficulty replay mode called Breakdown, and then there's a whole new map and way of playing in the final mode, Lifeline.This is by no means a perfect game, the graphics are definitely a bit dated, the UI leaves a bit to be desired, but holy crap, this game will satisfy. All the downsides to this game will fall by the wayside as you consider your next choice or try to save a sick base member, or desperately try to out run a zombie horde with a rucksack full of ammo on your back!Give this game a chance, and enjoy!TL;DR: 9/10"
