,Recommended,329430,32088982,Posted: 31 May,all,Cmdo.Delta,"Played this game for a little 15 hours within few days after purchase.So far, it's probably the best survival zombie game I've played. Its biggest downside is the lack of coop (at least 2 players would have been so awesome). If I understood well, they are making a ""State of Decay 2"" that will have coop, It's an amazing news. The only other concern I have about this game is there are few bugs there and there. The worse of them all: zombies clipping throught walls. It doesn't happen all the time but once in awhile and can catch you off guard.Those are the PROS and CONS for me. Indeed, you could disagree on some of them, it's a matter of taste and point of view:PROS:- 1 main story, 2 DLCs that bring endless mods for super extra replayability- Can control all survivors and have to level their abilities and gear them individually- Permadeath of survivors- No respawn of loot (can still establish outposts to help sustain but they wont remove need to scavenge)- Lot of weapons- Lot of kind of zombies- Many spots to establish base (all your choice where your survivors will live)- Lot of base upgrades- Survivor relies on stamina and health to survive. Poor management of those ressources can lead to quick death (survivors are never overpowered even when well trained and well geared)- Lot of cars with different specs (some are stronger, some are faster, some are balanced, some have better handling, etc)- Games generate random missions to keep you busy- When you roam around with your survivor, other survivors of your group are working aswell- When not playing the game, stuff keep happening to your survivor (they use ressources, can get sick.. maybe not die anymore). You get an update as soon as you launch the game again.CONS- Few bugs there and there like zombies clipping throught walls (not happening all the time but be aware it's possible)- No coopWhy I like this game more than many others like DayZ or WarZ or H1Z1? First: far less bugs. Then good mechanics around survivors (you have control on everyone of your community, permadeath, individual leveling/gearing, they keep living their lives while you are playing around, they keep living while game is closed)Why I prefer it over 7 days to die? 7DtD is probably one of the most serious game out there with the most serious devs. Just I was tired of the Minecraft style of building. State of decay offers the choice where to build base, allow base upgrades but you don't have to manually build stuff. You get ressources and let other survirors doing it. If you prefer a ""minecraft base building style"" then go with 7 days to die. If you don't want it, State of Decay is probably the best so far.A really good game. I got it 75% off which is absolute stealing. Even at full price, it would have worth it all the way. Definitively checking for State of decay 2."
