76561197989000593,Recommended,329430,29512973,Posted: 26 January,all,Drontti Edvard,"I played through the original game on the Xbox 360 and enjoyed it very much. If you also played it through I do not recommend the game, it is only good for new players or if you want to experience the DLC.Pros:-Gameplay: Simplistic yet addictive survival-Characters: Decent and after playing them for a while you will care about keeping them alive-Bases: You have the ability to change your home base-Limited amount of resources: All vehicles, resources etc. are limited so if you trash the car you are driving you better find a new one-Base Management: Upgrade your base with new ""buildings"" which provide you with buffs or completely new features-Multiple ""Main"" Characters: You play as all of your survivors and have to switch when others get tired. Makes you care also about others and you want to level them up for later.-Progression: Has a decent progression system with levels and ""perks"" which you can choose to differentiate between the specialization of each character.Cons-Horrible last gen console port!!!!The graphics are awful, the graphic settings are very lacking and the performance is very poor compared to the graphical fidelity. The game does not support 1440p and should be locked at 60fps. I have a 144hz 1440p monitor but I am forced to play at 1080p with locked 60 using Riva Tuner to get a decent gaming experience. This is unacceptable in the modern day. If the new game will be the same way I will refrain from buying it.-You Should Use a Controller:The gameplay is ok with a mouse and keyboard, but you really should use a controller for a more fluid gaming experience.-Bugs:Still has many of the same issues as the original Xbox 360 version had. Some bugs are minor others rather troublesome. I have not yet had massive issues, but the bugs are still annoying.-The Graphics:I mentioned them before, but they are just so awful I have to mention them twice. This game looks worse than the original Fable on the original Xbox. Fable had good graphics for the platform it was on and for the time it was made, this game doesn’t.ConclusionI have to recommend the game as I enjoy it very much. I have not yet found a better alternative for a action base-building walking dead type game so this game is the best one out there. It has its flaws, but if you are willing to look past them the game itself is great."
